news.title: PNB Housing Finance's net profit increases by 45.83% in Q2 FY24
news.para: PNB Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,779.40 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 5.70 per cent from Rs 1,683.43 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Oberoi Realty's sales bookings decline 17% to Rs 965 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: According to a regulatory filing on October 20, the company booked 151 units during the July-September period as against 132 units in the year-ago period.

news.title: Gujarat government sets up development authority for Becharaji region
news.para: About 825 hectares of Becharaji and its surrounding areas including Shankhalpur, Kalri, Ganeshpura, Pratapgarh, Finchdi, Dedana and Edala, villages have been included in the authority.

news.title: Madhra Pradesh HC allows housing board to pay Rs 435 crore dues
news.para: Justice Subodh Abhyankar directed MPHIDB to make the entire payment within a period of two weeks from the date of receipt of certified copy of this order. The MPHIDB shall make payment of Rs.6.54 crore directly to labour union as per settlement.

news.title: Navi Mumbai's AQI worsens, errant builders get notices
news.para: ​NMMC's additional city engineer Shirish Aradwad said a penalty of Rs 10/sqm will be levied on errant builders. "Our teams will visit construction sites, companies and quarries to check the sources of pollution," he said. Some six quarries are under the lens.

news.title: Mumbai: Ninth FIR on jailed builder for cheating 28 of Rs 40 crore
news.para: Tanna, who is lodged in Arthur Road jail, has been booked in nine offences registered all over Mumbai. Police said in most of these cases, Tanna and his family members allegedly sold flats to third parties.

news.title: Mumbai civic body directs infra, realty projects to follow pollution control measures
news.para: Construction, including private and infrastructure work led by the government, is currently underway at 6,000 locations and sites in Mumbai.

news.title: Diligent property tax payers to be rewarded: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: Pawar made the announcement at a programme organised by the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) on Saturday in which the civic body gave away awards worth Rs 1 crore to diligent tax payers.

news.title: Gurugram: 'Relief in three months' for buyers of nine stuck affordable housing projects
news.para: DTCP director general TL Satyaprakash said he has given directions to officials in the city to take steps to resolve the issues of homebuyers who purchased flats at projects linked to developers Mahira Homes, Ocean Seven Buildtech (OSB) and Orris Infrastructure.

news.title: Greenlighting construction in buffer zones in Bengaluru illegal: Experts
news.para: Amid the assurance by deputy chief minister DK Shivakumar that citizens owning plots in buffer zones around forest areas on the city’s outskirts will be allowed to construct buildings, legal experts and forest officials say the move will pave the way for a bitter confrontation.

news.title: Has the licence for lift in your flat, building in Kochi been renewed?
news.para: While this is undoubtedly a cause for concern, as per the data from four fire stations in the city, as many as 15 incidents of people getting stuck in lifts were reported in the past eight months this year.

news.title: DDA nudges landowners to opt for land pooling policy, finds few takers
news.para: Delhi's land pooling policy of 2018 aims to develop 105 villages that are divided into five zones - P-II, K-I, L, N and J. The land pooling, to be done by land owners through a consortium, requires 70% of the required land to be contiguous and without encumbrances.

news.title: Officials mull OTS scheme for illegal buildings in Ludhiana civic body limits
news.para: Due to the upcoming municipal corporation elections, it is expected that such policy will be introduced soon. However, the demand for an OTS policy has raised eyebrows of city activists, who have blamed the government for encouraging the violators by considering such a step.

news.title: Bengaluru development body encounters lacklustre response to auction from buyers
news.para: The BDA regularly auctions sites for revenue, and on October 16, it presented 123 corner and middle sites for auction across various layouts it had previously developed.

news.title: Record of land rights now available in 22 languages in Maharashtra
news.para: A senior official from the land department said the work on the project started early this year and the software has been made available on its website for all from August.

news.title: Anant Raj's net profit jumps 79% to Rs 60.37 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Anant Raj's total income rose to Rs 340.83 crore in the July-September period of 2023-24 from Rs 265.87 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, the company said in a regulatory filing on Saturday.

news.title: Ludhiana development body to begin process of regularisation of buildings soon
news.para: Under this policy, standalone buildings of educational, medical, commercial, farm houses, religious, social, charitable institutions, industries constructed outside municipal limits, outside Urban Estates and outside industrial focal points in the state will be covered.

news.title: Issue stop-work notices: BMC; experts suggest dashboard to name, shame builders
news.para: Experts, however, advocate for a public dashboard to be set up by the civic body where the list of repeat offenders can be published, on the lines of RBI releasing its list of defaulters. This move, they believe, would create a significant reputational deterrent for developers.

news.title: DLF & Shapoorji Pallonji take Hubtown, PNB to HC over South Mumbai project
news.para: A Rs 800-crore loan was secured to get on with construction and the stakes held by all three shareholders was pledged as additional security to PNB Housing Finance. When JHL failed to repay the loan, its account became a Non-Performing Asset in January 2022.

news.title: MCD penalises Godrej Properties' arm for violating NGT construction norms
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing on Saturday, Godrej Properties informed that its subsidiary Godrej Vestamark LLP on October 16 received an order in this regard under the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act 1957.
